{"id":8209,"date":"2012-10-15T14:31:03","date_gmt":"2012-10-15T18:31:03","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=8209"},"modified":"2023-03-24T12:03:46","modified_gmt":"2023-03-24T08:03:46","slug":"why-servants-despair","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/10\/15\/why-servants-despair\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Laughter: Why make My servants despair?"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Huraira reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, came out to a group of his companions while they were laughing and talking. The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>By the One in whose hand is my soul, if you knew what I knew, you would laugh little and weep often<\/strong>.\u201d The Prophet departed and people started weeping, so Allah Almighty revealed to him, \u201c<strong>O Muhammad, why have you made My servants despair?<\/strong>\u201d The Prophet returned and he said, \u201c<strong>Give glad tidings, follow the right course, and seek nearness\u00a0to Allah<\/strong>.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: al-Adab al-Mufrad lil-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 254<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <em><strong>Sahih\u00a0<\/strong><\/em>(authentic)\u00a0according to Al-Albani<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0647\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u200f \u062e\u064e\u0631\u064e\u062c\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0646\u064e\u0651\u0628\u0650\u064a\u064f\u0651 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0649 \u0631\u064e\u0647\u0652\u0637\u064d \u0645\u0650\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0635\u0652\u062d\u064e\u0627\u0628\u0650\u0647\u0650 \u064a\u064e\u0636\u0652\u062d\u064e\u0643\u064f\u0648\u0646\u064e \u0648\u064e\u064a\u064e\u062a\u064e\u062d\u064e\u062f\u064e\u0651\u062b\u064f\u0648\u